     mmkkffiiffoo - make fifos

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
     mmkkffiiffoo [--pp] _f_i_f_o__n_a_m_e ...

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
     MMkkffiiffoo creates the fifos requested, in the order specified, using mode
     0777.

     Options available are:

     --pp    Create intermediate directories as required.  If this option is not
	   specified, the full path prefix of each operand must already exist.

     MMkkffiiffoo requires write permission in the parent directory.

     MMkkffiiffoo exits 0 if successful, and >0 if an error occurred.

SSTTAANNDDAARRDDSS
     Mkfifo is POSIX 1003.2 compliant.
     This manual page derived from the POSIX 1003.2 manual page.

